java-rename-package - Java Package Renamer

USAGE:
    java-rename-package <from-package> <to-package>

DESCRIPTION:
    Rename Java package throughout project. Updates package declarations
    in files and renames corresponding directories.

ARGUMENTS:
    from-package
        Current package name (e.g., com.example.old)

    to-package
        New package name (e.g., com.example.new)

NOTE:
    Excludes .git and target directories.

EXAMPLES:
    java-rename-package com.example.old com.example.new
    java-rename-package foo.bar foo.baz
